This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and conversational models. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of an AI model. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of neural networks. It may also be classified under cs.SD (Sound) as affect can be conveyed through tone of voice. Lastly, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks to develop the model.
